Went to El Porton today with a few friends for a birthday party. In more than five years, this place has never ever let me down. The food is fast, the chips and salsa are free, and the bartender (older woman) who knows me always gives me an extra drink on the house. It's family-style service like this that keeps me coming back and always bringing my friends. The quesadillas are great, but so are the fajitas and basically everything else on the menu.  However, I wouldn't recommend this place for delivery. The delivery isn't "bad"... it's just... if you're going to pay El Porton prices, then you should get the El Porton experience. The restaurant's atmosphere makes it perfect for first dates, get-togethers, and family outings.  (It's just not a super kid friendly place).

I just moved to NYC, and I’ve been on the hunt for a great Mexican restaurant, in specific- the best guacamole in NYC. This was neither.  A couple weeks ago on a Sunday evening, I took my laptop and backpack to treat myself to a nice study date and some Mexican food. I had read the reviews, so I was optimistic.  When I was seated, it took over 10 minutes for them to bring the complimentary chips and salsa.  As I looked around, the restaurant wasn’t full, so I was a little confused. I’m  Then, I ordered guacamole and a grilled vegetable salad. It took another 15 minutes for them to bring the guacamole, and it took almost 40 minutes for my salad.  The guacamole had more opinions than avocado, and the grilled vegetables on the salad were cold  it even al dente.  Did it really take 40 minutes to throw a few peppers on the grill and then on a pile of lettuce?  It wasn’t just my experience that drove me to write this review. I watched other tables get their food, and two separate tables had to send entrees back because they were not correct.  The waiter even laughed and said “oh, whoops, we mixed your meal up with another table in the back.”  Personally, I think that’s unacceptable. What if someone has a food allergy or is vegetarian and is served something he/she/they didn’t order?  I also waited over 15 for my check when I asked for it.  I was willing to give this place a chance. Sometimes when the service is bad, the food is great or vice versa. But El Porton had bad service, and the food was not authentic or high quality.

Unfortunately, this restaurant either went thru new management, or key individuals who used to work here, quit or were let go. I went there for a margarita and a quesadilla. I used to go there before, and the Margarita used to be very well-made, tasty, and you can tell it was in fact a margarita, but I did notice that the guy who used to be the bartender was no longer there. The margarita not only taste bad (you couldn't tell that it was a margarita), I think the new bartender was cheap using the tequila to make it, because although I paid more than before, I did not get a buss or anything, and I don't drink very often. The quesadilla was just mediocre, which is unfortunate compared to when I had it some time ago. Food presentation was just messy, and the tortilla used to make the quesadilla was just soggy, instead of slightly toasted like before. I am very disappointed, and unfortunately, will not go there again. Its just too bad that once a restaurant used to be a favorite, due to different circumstances, becomes mediocre. I would have gladly gone there again and recommended in spite of new prices, provided that the drinks and food were of equal or better quality than I remember.

I would go for the margaritas alone, delicious first, boozy second and not sugary or syrupy like most places. I've also been treated to a free shot after a few drinks by the lovely staff.  They play major tv events of their big screen when on, they play fun music at night and smooth music during the day.  Delivery is pretty quick so it arrives in pretty good shape.  Love El Porton.
